	quest.1CF3499992DEAC9D.quest_desc: [
		"Organic compost is an accumulation of various residues used to make &9Rich Soil&r."
		""
		"&e-&r Once the decomposition process is complete, the organic compost turns into rich soil, which can be tilled for planting"
		"&e-&r Crops planted in rich soil grow significantly faster compared to normal farmlands"
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"&5* Decomposition&r "
		"To transform &9Organic Compost&r into &9Rich Soil&r, simply place it as a block in the world. Over time, it will naturally decompose into Rich Soil. This process can happen anywhere, but it can be accelerated under certain conditions:"
		""
		"&e-&r Exposure to direct sunlight"
		"&e-&r Direct contact with water (in adjacent blocks)"
		"&e-&r Presence of activator blocks nearby, such as:"
		"&e-&r Red or Brown Mushrooms, Mushroom Colonies, Mycelium and Podzol"
	]
	quest.1CF3499992DEAC9D.quest_subtitle: "&5Get Organic Compost"
	quest.1CF3499992DEAC9D.title: "Reusing Compounds"
	quest.237194A5F3216ABE.quest_subtitle: "&5 Find a  Weeping Well"
	quest.237194A5F3216ABE.title: "Among the depths"
	quest.250E31A75164ECFE.quest_desc: [
		"Mortar is the base of the rustic oven, collect good quantities to be able to build yours."
		""
		"The most efficient ways to obtain mortar in the early game are by collecting seashells on beaches or by chopping bones on the &9cutting table&r using a pickaxe."
	]
	quest.250E31A75164ECFE.quest_subtitle: "&5Craft Mortar"
	quest.250E31A75164ECFE.title: "Molding Clay"
	quest.260EC27B5BE80815.quest_subtitle: "&5Get a Basic Alchemical Crucible"
	quest.260EC27B5BE80815.title: "Basic Alchemy"
	quest.2610D92D5D724454.quest_desc: [
		"Storing energy is essential to your Techpack experience's longevity."
		""
		"Your first way to store energy is the &9\"Battery Box\"&r a simple box of zinc cells that can store up to &9500,000 RF&r."
		""
		"&e-&r the battery box can input AND output on the front and back faces. (both faces are I/O)"
		""
		"&5>&r Buffer term explanation"
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"&9Buffers&r"
		""
		"It's also worth mentioning the term \"Buffer,\" which will be used later. Simply put, a buffer refers to internal storage which depending on the context can maintained in the event of a power outage, for example."
		""
		"This term is often used to refer to batteries and tanks, but it can also be commonly used to describe how much energy storage a machine can have."
	]
	quest.2610D92D5D724454.quest_subtitle: "&5Craft a Battery Box"
	quest.2610D92D5D724454.title: "Storing RF"
	quest.276625D22CD9F37B.title: "Wrough Iron Arsenal"
	quest.281FDAC6E901BD9E.quest_desc: [
		"Furnaces are a somewhat advanced technology in this world, so you will need to build a &9Rustic Oven&r."
		""
		"A Rustic Oven is a multi-block structure that works similarly to a furnace, but with minor differences in how items are inserted and removed from hatches."
		""
		"To make a Rustic Oven, you will need to build one, which you can view by clicking on the block with a &9Blueprint&r."
		""
		"&e-&r Consider using tiny item bus to make your first Rustic Oven"
		""
		"&5>&r Multi-Blocks Structures "
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"&9Multi-Blocks Structures&r"
		""
		"Multi-blocks are structures that work like machines, but have some differences such as:"
		""
		"&e-&r &9Having hatches&r: Blocks that are outputs and inputs for items, fluids or energy. &e-&r &9Have a controller&r: Main block of the structure"
		"&e-&r &9Follow a construction model&r: Each multiblock has a different structure"
		""
		"&5>&r How to Build a Rustic Oven"
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"&9How to Build a Rustic Oven&r"
		""
		"L = Layer"
		""
		"&9L1&r: -- &9L2&r: -- &9L3&r:"
		"&5‚Ė†‚Ė†‚Ė†&r - &8‚Ė†‚Ė†‚Ė†&r - #&8‚Ė†&r#"
		"&5‚Ė†&r&6‚Ė†&r&5‚Ė†&r - &8‚Ė†&r#&8‚Ė†&r - &8‚Ė†&r#&8‚Ė†&r"
		"&5‚Ė†&r&a‚Ė†&r&5‚Ė†&r - &8‚Ė†‚Ė†‚Ė†&r - #&8‚Ė†&r#"
		""
		"&e-&r &a‚Ė†&r: &9Rustic Oven&r (Controller)"
		"&e-&r &5‚Ė†&r: Can be filled by Mortar or Any item hatch (either input or output)"
		"&e-&r &8‚Ė†&r: Can be filled by Mortar"
		"&e-&r &6‚Ė†&r: Can be filled by Campfire"
		"&e-&r #: Empty"
	]
	quest.281FDAC6E901BD9E.quest_subtitle: "&5Build a rustic oven"
	quest.281FDAC6E901BD9E.title: "Its a Furnace?"
	quest.2878606D4273FB1C.quest_desc: [
		"Gluttony is a small friend from the other side of the void who consumes food and generates food-related spirits."
		""
		"&e-&r Can input items on the front"
		"&e-&r Can output items on the bottom"
		""
		"&5>&r Lore: The Hungry Guy"
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"&9Lore: The Hungry Guy&r"
		""
		"It mysteriously comes to life when an organic component is dropped in the Weeping Well. Perhaps he belongs to a species that lives on the other side."
		""
		"It's interesting that sometimes he generates &9Lustrous Pearls&r. I don't know what it is yet, but I think it's important."
	]
	quest.2878606D4273FB1C.quest_subtitle: "&5Get an Glutton"
	quest.2878606D4273FB1C.title: "The Hungry Guy"
	quest.2AC97EB35CA8AC08.quest_desc: [
		"&9Wrough iron&r is a variation of iron used to make better tools, with more durability and in some cases, more damage."
		""
		"&e -&r Wrough iron is also used to make things related to tools"
	]
